When does MIT apply vs. Apache 2.0?
-----------------------------------

By default, assume ALL AUGMANITAI code is Apache 2.0. MIT applies only to
files that explicitly declare MIT in their SPDX header. A file is MIT-only
if it contains:

    SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

at the top. Otherwise it is Apache 2.0.

Why offer both?
---------------

MIT is simpler and has no explicit patent grant. Apache 2.0 is more robust
for larger projects because of its patent grant and defensive termination.
For small utility snippets (e.g., one-file helper scripts contributed by
third parties who prefer MIT), MIT is acceptable.

